<item>
            <title>[MATH-927] GammaDistribution cloning broken</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-927</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Serializing a GammaDistribution and deserializing it, does not result in a cloned distribution that produces the same samples.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cause: GammaDistribution inherits from AbstractRealDistribution, which implements Serializable. AbstractRealDistribution has random, in which we have a Well19937c instance, which inherits from AbstractWell. AbstractWell implements Serializable. AbstractWell inherits from BitsStreamGenerator, which is not Serializable, but does have a private field &apos;nextGaussian&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Solution: Make BitStreamGenerator implement Serializable as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This probably affects other distributions as well.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
